      "name": "What is RAG and why does Devometric use it?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation) is an AI architecture that enhances large language models by giving them access to external knowledge bases. Instead of relying solely on training data, RAG systems can retrieve and reference up-to-date, specific information. Devometric uses RAG to ensure our assessments and recommendations reflect the latest AI tools, techniques, and best practices in software development."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How accurate is the AI Nativeness Score?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "The score is designed to be directionally accurate and actionable rather than a precise measurement. Our assessment methodology was developed by analyzing patterns from thousands of developer interactions with AI tools. The score is most valuable for tracking individual progress over time, identifying specific skill gaps, and comparing relative strengths across the four dimensions."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Which LLM does Devometric use?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Devometric primarily uses Claude by Anthropic, currently one of the highest-performing models for nuanced conversation and technical understanding. We specifically chose Claude for its strong reasoning capabilities and ability to maintain context across complex, multi-turn conversations. Enterprise customers with BYOK (Bring Your Own Key) can use their own Anthropic API key."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How does Devometric ensure assessment quality and consistency?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "We use carefully engineered system prompts that guide the AI through a structured assessment methodology. These prompts ensure consistent evaluation criteria across all assessments, natural conversational flow, comprehensive coverage of all four scoring dimensions, and adaptation to individual responses without losing assessment integrity."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Is my assessment data used to train AI models?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "No. Your assessment conversations are not used to train any AI models. We use Anthropic's API with data retention disabled, meaning your conversations are not stored by the AI provider after processing. Your data is stored securely in our system solely for providing assessment results, tracking progress, and generating personalized recommendations."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How often should team members retake the assessment?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "We recommend quarterly assessments for most teams. This cadence allows enough time to implement recommendations and develop new skills while keeping pace with the rapidly evolving AI landscape. Teams actively focused on AI adoption initiatives may benefit from monthly check-ins."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How does Devometric calculate the AI Nativeness Score?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "The AI Nativeness Score is a 100-point score calculated across four dimensions: Tool Awareness (0-25 points) measuring knowledge of AI coding tools, Daily Integration (0-25 points) measuring how embedded AI is in workflows, Prompt Skills (0-25 points) measuring ability to communicate with AI systems, and Critical Thinking (0-25 points) measuring ability to evaluate and improve AI output."
      }
    },
